The paper deals with facial motion retargeting, which is a problem in computer graphics and vision. The use of convolutional neural networks for 2D face alignment and 3D face reconstruction suggests that the paper belongs to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also involves designing a novel multitask learning framework, which falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The use of 3D morphable model (3DMM) parameters and the transfer of facial performance to another 3D character suggests that the paper may also belong to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. The paper involves joint face detection and motion retargeting for multiple faces, which suggests that it may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the use of deep learning techniques and the design of an end-to-end network suggest that the paper may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
